4. Tile Model (Final Definition)
4.1 Storage Model
Tiles are stored as:
2km x 2km bounding boxes
min_lat, max_lat
min_lng, max_lng
Used for:
Coverage bookkeeping
last_scanned tracking
Density analysis

4.2 Crawl Query Geometry
Runtime query:
Nearby Search(center_point, radius = 2000m)
Where:
center_point = tile centroid.
This hybrid model is intentional:
Nearby is radius-based
Bounding boxes enable coverage governance
PostGIS enables viewport filtering

5. API Usage Model (Validated)
5.1 Maximum Theoretical Calls
180 tiles × 3 categories = 540 calls
But monthly cap = 400.
Therefore:
Weekly slice must be tuned.

5.2 Weekly Execution Model
Monthly refresh achieved via 4 weekly runs.
Target per week:
~33 tiles maximum
33 × 3 = 99 calls/week
99 × 4 weeks = 396 calls/month
Within cap.
Weekly tile slice must never exceed 33.
Hard rule:
IF weekly_tiles × 3 > 100
→ adjust slice downward.

5.3 Hard Stop Rule
Inside crawl:
IF api_calls >= 400 → STOP
Status = STOPPED_CAP
No overrun allowed.

