9. Idempotency Guarantee
Crawler must be idempotent.
Requirements:
UPSERT by place_id
last_seen updated on each encounter
score recalculated deterministically
No duplicate records possible
If scheduled function runs twice:
No corruption
No double counting
No state drift

10. Scoring Model
Versioned scoring:
score_version = 1

base = ln(reviews_count + 1) * 40
rating_component = rating * 10

penalty:
   PROFESSIONAL = 30
   SOCIAL_ONLY = 10
   NO_WEBSITE = 0

bonus:
   RESTAURANT = 10
   HAIR = 8
   HOME_SERVICES = 12

score = base + rating_component - penalty + bonus
Future changes increment score_version.

11. Map Loading Model
11.1 Viewport-Based Query
On map load:
Query only businesses within current viewport bounds.
Use:
PostGIS ST_Intersects
or bounding box operator &&
Debounce: 400–600ms on pan/zoom.

11.2 No Full Dataset Preload
System does NOT load all businesses on initial render.
Prevents:
Memory overload
Heatmap lag
Mobile slowdown

